import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['cx'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude Coordinates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude coordinates of the London borough centroids?')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['cy'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude Coordinates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude coordinates of the London borough centroids?')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.sort_values(by='cx', ascending=False)
    ax = plt.bar(data['name'], data['cx'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which London borough has the highest longitude coordinate?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(data['cx'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max Longitude: {data['cx'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.sort_values(by='cy', ascending=False)
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', x='name', y='cy', rot=90)
    ax.axhline(y=data['cy'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['cy'].max():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('Which London borough has the highest latitude coordinate?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
